  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do if I forget my user id and password of forex card HDFC?",
  "response": "If you forget your user ID and password for your HDFC forex card, you can follow these steps to recover them:\n\n### Recovering User ID:\n1. **Visit the HDFC Bank Website**: Go to the official HDFC Bank website.\n2. **Navigate to Forex Card Section**: Look for the section related to Forex Cards.\n3. **Find the Login Section**: Go to the login page for Forex Card users.\n4. **Select \"Forgot User ID\"**: You should see an option that says \"Forgot User ID\" or something similar. Click on it.\n5. **Enter Required Information**: You will be asked to enter details like your card number, date of birth, and registered mobile number or email ID.\n6. **OTP Verification**: An OTP (One-Time Password) will be sent to your registered mobile number or email. Enter the OTP to verify your identity.\n7. **Retrieve User ID**: Once verified, your user ID will be displayed on the screen or sent to your registered contact details.\n\n### Recovering Password:\n1. **Visit the HDFC Bank Website**: Go to the official HDFC Bank website.\n2. **Navigate to Forex Card Section**: Look for the section related to Forex Cards.\n3. **Find the Login Section**: Go to the login page for Forex Card users.\n4. **Select \"Forgot Password\"**: You should see an option that says \"Forgot Password\" or something similar. Click on it.\n5. **Enter User ID**: Enter your user ID that you just recovered.\n6. **Enter Required Information**: You will be asked to enter details like your card number, date of birth, and registered mobile number or email ID.\n7. **OTP Verification**: An OTP will be sent to your registered mobile number or email. Enter the OTP to verify your identity.\n8. **Set New Password**: You will be prompted to set a new password. Follow the on-screen instructions to create a new password.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Customer Support**: If you face any issues during the recovery process, you can contact HDFC Bank\u2019s customer support. They have dedicated helplines and email support for such issues.\n- **Security**: Always ensure you are on the official HDFC Bank website and do not share your personal details with anyone claiming to be from the bank unless you have initiated the contact.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to recover your user ID and reset your password for your HDFC forex card.",
